# Exercise 2.8

## Base case

Observe that 

$$
\begin{align*}
  2^{1 - 1}(a^1 + b^1) &= 2^0(a^1 + b^1) \\
  &= a^1 + b^1 \\
  &\geq (a + b)
\end{align*}
$$

## Inductive hypothesis

Assume that $\forall k \in \mathbb{N}$ such that $1 \leq k < n$

$$
\begin{align*}
  2^{k - 1}(a^k + b^k) \geq (a + b)^k
\end{align*}
$$

## Inductive step

$$
\begin{align*}
  2^{n - 1}(a^n + b^n) \geq (a + b)^k
\end{align*}
$$
